          "span": "Maximum likelihood estimation uses the log-likelihood as its objective and selects a parameter value that maximizes it:\n\n\\[\n\\widehat{\\theta}_{\\mathrm{MLE}} = \\operatorname*{arg\\,max}_{\\theta}\\, \\ell(\\theta).\n\\]"
        },
        {
          "lecture_id": "statistics_estimation_001",
          "span": "A statistical model is a family of probability distributions indexed by an unknown parameter \\(\\theta\\)."
        }
      ],
      "rationale": "The MLE Estimator formula explicitly defines the estimator as the argmax of the log-likelihood, which is derived from the statistical model. The formula formalizes the concept of a statistical model by providing a concrete estimation procedure."
